In this implementation, we use two stacks to simulate a queue's behavior. The `enqueue` method adds elements to the end of the queue by pushing them onto `stack1`, while the `dequeue` method removes elements from the front of the queue by first transferring elements from `stack1` to `stack2` (if `stack2` is empty) and then popping elements off `stack2`.

